We had lunch here on a Sunday. There is plenty of space in the dining room and an interesting mural on the wall. The gyro wrap was tasty and big, but it could benefit from some *good* lettuce. My date had an egg sandwich with cheese and avocado. It was straightforward and fine. The prices were fair ($12 for the two of us) and the food was totally good grill-style food. Maybe check it out if you ever find yourself hungry at Stanley's Produce.
